- Researched HF blocker workarounds. Findings: serverless/provider routing is catalog-driven, not fixed by metadata alone; public `google/gemma-4-E2B-it` was not deployed by any Inference Provider at research time; default Toolkit `handler.py`/`requirements.txt` cannot reliably fix failures before handler import; TGI supported-model docs list Gemma/Gemma2/Gemma3 but not Gemma4; regular Gemma4 may need vLLM or a task/loader class aligned with Gemma4 docs (`AutoModelForImageTextToText`/multimodal path vs `AutoModelForCausalLM`); public Docker Hub is the lowest-friction custom-image registry path.
- Ran zero-cost local Gemma4 validation. Active project/system Python lacks `transformers`, `torch`, `accelerate`, and `safetensors`; local GPU is RTX 4060 Laptop 8 GiB, below safe budget for 9.5 GiB weights. Repo structure is complete: `Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration`, `model_type=gemma4`, `Gemma4Processor`, `GemmaTokenizer`, chat template, and weights present. No loader/chat-template could be executed until an isolated bleeding-edge Transformers/Torch environment exists.
- Created isolated temp env `/tmp/opencode/gemma4-dep-venv` and validated regular Gemma4 with `transformers==5.8.0.dev0` from git main commit `52b82b2`, `torch==2.12.0+cu130`, `torchvision==0.27.0`, `accelerate==1.13.0`, `safetensors==0.7.0`, `sentencepiece==0.2.1`. `AutoProcessor`/`AutoTokenizer` load successfully; processor and tokenizer chat templates work with `enable_thinking=False`; `AutoConfig` maps to `Gemma4Config`; `AutoModelForCausalLM`, `AutoModelForImageTextToText`, and `AutoModelForMultimodalLM` all map to `Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration`; meta init via `AutoModelForImageTextToText.from_config` succeeds. `torchvision` is required because `Gemma4VideoProcessor` import failed without it. Full local generation remains unsafe on 8 GiB VRAM.
